---
import Layout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from 'astrowind:config';

const crumbs = [
  { name: 'Home', href: '/' },
  { name: 'R&D Center', href: '/randdcenter' },
  { name: 'Textile Quality Assurance Lab' },
];

const metadata = {
  title: `Textile Quality Assurance Lab — AATCC/ASTM-Compliant Fabric Testing & Certification | ${SITE.name}`,
  description: `Independent quality verification for functional fabrics. Tensile testing, color fastness, dimensional stability, and material certification. Contact our quality lab for third-party testing.`,
};
---

<Layout metadata={metadata} breadcrumbs={crumbs}>
  <section class="px-6 sm:px-6 py-16 sm:py-20 mx-auto max-w-5xl">
    <a href="/randdcenter" class="text-sm text-gray-500 hover:underline">&larr; Back to R&D Center</a>
    <div class="mt-4 grid md:grid-cols-5 gap-10">
      <div class="md:col-span-3">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-primary uppercase tracking-wider">Lab 06</p>
        <h1 class="mt-2 text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold">Textile Quality Assurance Lab</h1>
        <p class="mt-3 text-lg text-muted">Independent verification — every test passed before delivery</p>
      </div>
      <div class="md:col-span-2">
        <img
          src="/images/seekingtex/factory/fabric-quality-lab.webp"
          alt="Seekingtex textile quality assurance laboratory"
          class="w-full h-48 object-cover rounded-xl"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="px-6 sm:px-6 pb-12 mx-auto max-w-4xl prose prose-gray dark:prose-invert">
    <h2>Trust, but verify</h2>
    <p>
      Every fabric roll that leaves our facility carries the certification that it has passed a defined set of quality
      inspections and material tests. Our Textile Quality Assurance Lab is an independent function within the organisation —
      it reports directly to the managing director, not to production — ensuring that no commercial pressure can
      compromise the inspection gate. If a material batch or a finished fabric does not meet the published specification,
      the lab has the authority to halt shipment until the non-conformance is resolved.
    </p>
    <p>
      The lab operates under a quality management system aligned with ISO 9001 principles, and our test methods are
      based on AATCC, ASTM, and ISO standards wherever applicable. We maintain detailed records of every test performed,
      creating a complete traceability chain from raw material receipt to final fabric delivery.
    </p>

    <h2>Test equipment and capabilities</h2>
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>Equipment</th><th>Tests Performed</th><th>Standard / Method</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr
          ><td>Universal testing machine (50 kN)</td><td
            >Tensile strength (fabric), seam strength, tear propagation</td
          ><td>ASTM D5034, ASTM D1683, ASTM D2261</td></tr
        >
        <tr
          ><td>Color spectrophotometer</td><td
            >Delta-E color measurement, shade sorting, color fastness to light/wash/rub</td
          ><td>AATCC TM110, AATCC TM61, AATCC TM8</td></tr
        >
        <tr
          ><td>Dimensional stability tester</td><td>Fabric shrinkage after laundering, relaxation, and steaming</td><td
            >AATCC 135 / AATCC 150</td
          ></tr
        >
        <tr
          ><td>Hydrostatic head tester</td><td>Water penetration resistance of fabric (0-5000 mbar)</td><td>ISO 811 / AATCC TM127</td
          ></tr
        >
        <tr
          ><td>Digital thickness gauge & micrometer</td><td
            >Fabric thickness, coating thickness, film thickness</td
          ><td>ASTM D1777</td></tr
        >
        <tr
          ><td>Environmental chamber</td><td
            >Temperature/humidity conditioning (-40 °C to +80 °C) for accelerated aging tests</td
          ><td>ASTM D573, AATCC TM186</td></tr
        >
        <tr
          ><td>Martindale abrasion tester</td><td>Abrasion resistance, pilling resistance</td><td
            >ASTM D4966 / ISO 12947</td
          ></tr
        >
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2>The inspection gates — from material to delivery</h2>
    <p>
      Every fabric lot follows a defined quality plan with mandatory inspection points. No lot can skip a gate; each gate
      must be signed off by a quality inspector before the next stage begins.
    </p>

    <div class="not-prose my-8">
      <div class="relative">
        <div class="absolute left-4 top-0 bottom-0 w-0.5 bg-blue-200 dark:bg-blue-800"></div>
        <div class="space-y-6 relative">
          {
            [
              {
                gate: 'Gate 1',
                label: 'Incoming material inspection',
                desc: 'Fiber batch, coating chemicals, finish additives — all checked against incoming specification before release to production.',
              },
              {
                gate: 'Gate 2',
                label: 'In-process fabric inspection',
                desc: 'First-off greige fabric inspected (visual + weight) at start of each production run.',
              },
              {
                gate: 'Gate 3',
                label: 'Color & finish verification',
                desc: 'Finished fabric measured for color accuracy (Delta-E), coating weight, and finish uniformity.',
              },
              {
                gate: 'Gate 4',
                label: 'Pre-delivery inspection',
                desc: 'Complete fabric roll inspected: width, weight, defects, shade banding. 50-point checklist per roll.',
              },
              {
                gate: 'Gate 5',
                label: 'Final certification',
                desc: 'Test reports compiled, inspection records reviewed, Certificate of Conformance issued.',
              },
            ].map((g) => (
              <div class="flex gap-4">
                <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-blue-600 text-white flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-bold z-10">
                  {g.gate}
                </div>
                <div class="flex-1 p-3 rounded-lg bg-white dark:bg-gray-950 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800">
                  <p class="text-sm font-semibold">{g.label}</p>
                  <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-1">{g.desc}</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            ))
          }
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2>Key quality metrics (2025 rolling average)</h2>
    <div class="not-prose my-8 grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-4">
      <div class="p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 bg-white dark:bg-gray-950 text-center">
        <span class="block text-2xl font-bold text-blue-600">99.7 %</span>
        <span class="text-xs text-gray-500">First-pass yield (fabric lot)</span>
      </div>
      <div class="p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 bg-white dark:bg-gray-950 text-center">
        <span class="block text-2xl font-bold text-blue-600">&lt; 0.2 %</span>
        <span class="text-xs text-gray-500">Defect rate (linear metre)</span>
      </div>
      <div class="p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 bg-white dark:bg-gray-950 text-center">
        <span class="block text-2xl font-bold text-blue-600">100 %</span>
        <span class="text-xs text-gray-500">Fabric rolls inspected before shipment</span>
      </div>
      <div class="p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 bg-white dark:bg-gray-950 text-center">
        <span class="block text-2xl font-bold text-blue-600">ISO 9001</span>
        <span class="text-xs text-gray-500">Quality management system compliance</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2>Our quality team</h2>
    <p>
      The lab is staffed by a quality manager (10 years in textile QA, ASQ Certified Quality Engineer), two quality
      inspectors (each with Level 2 certification in textile inspection), and a materials technician responsible for all
      physical testing. The team undergoes annual proficiency testing through an independent third-party provider to
      ensure that our test results remain accurate and reproducible.
    </p>

    <h2>Independent testing for clients</h2>
    <p>
      Our Textile Quality Assurance Lab is available for independent testing services. If you need to verify a fabric
      specification, validate a new finish, or obtain a third-party test report for a procurement
      qualification, we can perform the tests to the applicable standard and issue a certified test report.
    </p>
    <p>Examples of recent third-party testing work:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        Color fastness comparison of five competitive dye systems for a European apparel brand's quality assurance
        programme.
      </li>
      <li>
        Accelerated aging study (UV + thermal cycling) for a new UPF-enhanced polyester formulation, with regular interim
        measurements at 500 h intervals.
      </li>
      <li>Dimensional stability validation of 50 prototype fabric constructions for a new performance wear line.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Our commitment to you</h2>
    <p>
      When you receive a {SITE.name} fabric, you also receive its quality dossier — a compiled record of the test results that
      apply to your specific fabric lot. Fiber certificate, color fastness report, dimensional stability test results, and pre-delivery inspection
      checklist. Every number is traceable. Every inspector is identified. This is not just paperwork — it is our promise
      that what we delivered is what we specified.
    </p>
    <p>
      If you ever have a quality concern, you can contact the lab directly — the contact details are printed on your
      certificate of conformance. We take every query seriously and commit to a formal investigation within 48 hours.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="px-6 sm:px-6 pb-20 mx-auto max-w-4xl text-center">
    <div class="rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-900 p-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold">Need independent testing or quality verification?</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted">
        Our lab accepts third-party testing work — contact us with your requirements.
      </p>
      <a
        href="/contact"
        class="mt-4 inline-block px-6 py-3 bg-primary text-white font-semibold rounded-md hover:bg-primary/90"
        >Contact the quality lab</a
      >
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
